Yep, this is due to the micrometer contract: https://github.com/micrometer-metrics/micrometer/blob/37360582d35947fbc4c7479886ce6ebbe6a8086a/implementations/micrometer-registry-elastic/src/main/java/io/micrometer/elastic/ElasticConfig.java#L40 .
The default config map returns always null so that the default values are used. For example you can see in the Springboot impl that the default value is null
    @Value(value = "${kogito.addon.monitoring.elastic.indexDateFormat:#{null}}")

